commText: Welcome back for the chase. Interestingly, Rahul is out there. He wasn't supposed to keep. He kept and now he wasn't supposed to open. But is opening. QDK will be alongside him. Nandre Burger is the Impact Sub for RR.

Riyan Parag - The main goal was to take the game deep, the wicket was staying very low and was assisting the spinners. My mindset was simple, the way I play my domestic game, I just practiced well in the last 10 days and implemented it on the ground today. Sanga was pretty clear, I had a chat with him, Sanju bhaiya and the management, I wanted that clarity, I had played at 4 in the domestic season.

Samson in his first match of an IPL season since 2020 74(32) vs CSK 2020 119(63) vs PK 2021 55(27) vs SRH 2022 55(32) vs SRH 2023 82*(52) vs LSG 2024 Pace vs spin in Royals' innings Pace: 3/129 in 11 overs (ER 11.73) Spin: 1/63 in 9 overs (ER 7.00) Most 50+ scores for Royals in all T20s 23 J Buttler (71 innings) 23 A Rahane (99) 23*S Samson (127) 16 S Watson (81)

17:23 Local Time, 11:53 GMT, 17:23 IST: RR have put up a good score. Though they would feel, they could have gotten a few more. But LSG bowlers got their acts together in the last 5 overs and bowled to certain plans to restrict the score a little. The last four overs prior to the 20th saw 36 runs being scored. Samson didn't get much strike also. That also didn't help. Earlier, Buttler and Jaiswal got starts but threw it away. RR's number 4 in the form of Parag batted fearlessly and scored 43 in quick time. LSG bowlers missed their lengths at times and that was taken severe toll of when the Samson-Parag partnership was on. The chase will be a tough one. But expect Rahul and co. to give a good account of themselves.
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 2 runs, they will finish with a couple. Good end for RR. 14 runs off the last over. Was a fuller ball, Samson whips it wide of long leg for a brace. Samson's RR end with 193
Mohsin Khan to Samson, SIX, slower, length delivery, Samson camps on the back foot and slams it over deep cover. Was hit hard and long. He has played a tremendous knock so far
Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, punches that through the off-side for a single. Was a back of a length delivery from Mohsin Khan and Dhruv Jurel managed to send it off the back foot

Mohsin Khan to Dhruv Jurel, FOUR, shorter, slower, Dhruv Jurel goes for the pull and plays it fine enough for a four. Just needed some bat on it and got it. RR will take it with open arms as fours and sixes have been tough to come in the last few overs
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 1 run, slower shorter delivery, Samson looked to pull and was too early into the shot. Mistimed it down to long-on
Mohsin Khan to Samson, no run, starts the over with a dot. LSG and their bowlers are looking to finish well. The ball curled away and Samson looked to slog but missed making contact
Mohsin Khan [3.0-0-31-1] is back into the attack

Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, slices a short ball, the man at long-off came in charging in. But I guess the ball dropped in front of him and hit his body to ricochet away a little. They get a brace. Was a short ball, outside off, Dhruv Jurel looked to pull and got a top-edge. Naveen-ul-Haq has bowled out here. Infact, that's a drop! The fielder got too close to the ball in the end as he put in the slide to take it

Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, no run, excellent finish for LSG so far. They have given few wides. But the plan of bowling well outside off has worked. Slower one well outside off, Dhruv Jurel looks to slog sweep it and misses. Samson walked up to Dhruv Jurel and has few words to say to his partner
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, 1 run, sliced down to deep point for a single. Very full and wide. Samson opened the face of the bat but failed to get the gap
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, very full again, Dhruv Jurel jams the drive down to deep cover for a single. Failed to get under it as Naveen-ul-Haq nailed the wide yorker
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, drills it through the off-side and gets a brace. Was a slower, shorter delivery and Dhruv Jurel slapped it over cover. There was no pace on that delivery
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, wide, and wided again. Very full, very wide and easy call this time

Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, wide, Rahul reviews for a wide. That was short, slower, wider, Dhruv Jurel looked to slash at it and missed. The batter walked across his sticks but how far did he go? The review is lost and has been wided
Naveen-ul-Haq to Dhruv Jurel, no run, very full, very wide, Jurel looks to dig it out and misses. They don't review for a wide
Naveen-ul-Haq [3.0-0-33-2] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Samson, SIX, slammed! Sixer to end the over. Towering blow from Samson as he had the license to send it away. He will look to finish strong here

Yash Thakur to Samson, no ball, and that's unfortunate! No-ball. Was called as a leg-side wide after he had overstepped, LSG though reviewed, but the replay suggested that Thakur had overstepped, by a very small margin
Yash Thakur to Samson, 2 runs, very full, from round the wicket and Samson walks across his sticks and clips it wide of deep square. They get a brace
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, gets it behind square for a single. Walked across his sticks, then figured out was a slower ball and nudged it wide of short fine
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, mistimes the heave down to deep mid for a single. Was a length delivery on the pads
Yash Thakur to Dhruv Jurel, 1 run, one more to the tally. Was banged in short, cramped for room and Dhruv Jurel somehow mistimed the pull for a single
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, fuller ball, at the sticks, pushed down to long-off for a single
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack

Ravi Bishnoi to Dhruv Jurel, SIX, that's the confidence that we are used to from Dhruv Jurel! But he almost holed out. The man at long-on put in the dive to his left but failed to grab it. Was well flighted outside off, Dhruv Jurel knelt down and slammed it down the ground. The fielder threw himself but failed to stop it. RR needed it as they continue their march towards peak 200!
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhruv Jurel, 2 runs, two more. Gets off the mark. Was a googly on the pads, Dhruv Jurel
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhruv Jurel, no run, googly. Spuns in, stabbed down to the man at short third man
Dhruv Jurel, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, out Caught by Rahul!! Hetmyer didn't realize he nicked it. The onfield umpire also took his time signalling it out. But Hetmyer thought he hadn't edged it. But UltraEdge showed a little spike and Hetmyer has to go without disturbing the scorers much. Fourth one down for RR. They needed Hetmyer to play a good cameo but they have lost him and a review as well. Hetmyer c Rahul b Ravi Bishnoi 5(7)
Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Review taken. Hetmyer is bemused that he has been given out caught behind. Was a tossed up googly. Hetmyer looked to push at it and has he edged it? Yes, he has. There is a spike and he has to go.
Ravi Bishnoi to Hetmyer, no run, tossed up delivery, googly, Hetmyer stabs it down to point. They don't get a single despite a few calls
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, gets that down to long-on for a single as that was dropped flatter. Samson went back to punch it down to the fielder
Ravi Bishnoi [3.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack

Ayush Badoni to Samson, 1 run, pushes it down to long-on for a single. Was a flatter one, at the sticks, Samson went back to get it down to long-on. Good over from Ayush Badoni as he concedes only 6 runs off it. Excellent move from Rahul and worked as well. Don't think he will bowl another one. Or will he?
Ayush Badoni to Hetmyer, 1 run, off the inner-half of the bat and down to long-on for a single as he tried to push at it
Ayush Badoni to Hetmyer, 2 runs, spanks the drive as that was tossed up well outside off. The man at deep cover dives and stops it, Got the room to put it away
Ayush Badoni to Hetmyer, no run, flighted one, spins in, Hetmyer looks to nudge it and misses. There was a bit of an appeal but turned down
Ayush Badoni to Samson, 1 run, gets that down to deep mid for a single as that was a quicker one at the sticks. Badoni in the 16th over. That's a gamble
Ayush Badoni to Hetmyer, 1 run, whips that down to deep mid for a single. The fielder in the deep put in the slide and stopped it. Was a flatter one at the sticks
Ayush Badoni, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Naveen-ul-Haq to Hetmyer, 1 run, tucks the ball down off the pads for a single. Hetmyer is off the mark. That was a pace on delivery from Naveen-ul-Haq
Shimron Hetmyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Time-out. RR have lost a huge wicket. Parag could have been dangerous going into the last lap. But he is gone now. Samson is there and RR will need fresh wings from the other end to take them to higher planes. Hetmyer and Jurel have an ideal set up to walk in and just throw caution to the winds.

Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, out Caught by (sub)Hooda!! One shot too many from Parag. He has to go now. That was a short ball, dug in, Riyan Parag went for the pull and got a top-edge. The balance wasn't there as he made contact. The ball went very high and the man from deep square came in, got under it and took it with elan. Hooda had no qualms. Huge wicket for LSG as Riyan Parag was taking the game away alongside his skipper. Riyan Parag c (sub)Hooda b Naveen-ul-Haq 43(29) [4s-1 6s-3]
Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, SIX, huge! That's outta here. Parag forehands it over long-off. Was a slower, shorter delivery, outside off and Riyan Parag used his bottom hand to smash it over long-off. All power from Riyan Parag. He is looking threatening here
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, 1 run, gets that down to long-off for a single. Very wide, very full, cue-ended down to long-off. Was a slower one
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, wide, wided again. These sundries will come back to hurt them for sure. Length delivery, well wide outside off and Samson never made an attempt to play that one

Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, 1 run, through the off-side for a single. Again gets a widish delivery well outside off and Riyan Parag sliced it down to deep cpver for a single. Failed to place it better

Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, FOUR, four more. Waits on the shortish slower delivery, Riyan Parag goes back and slashes it past point for a four. That was a slower delivery well disguised but Riyan Parag waited on it and put it away. Runs coming thick and fast for RR
Naveen-ul-Haq to Riyan Parag, wide, fuller length delivery, well outside off and left alone for it to be wided. Riyan Parag didn't chase it
Naveen-ul-Haq [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack

Yash Thakur to Samson, FOUR, walks across his sticks, gets hold of the shortish delivery and scoops it over short fine. Lovely improvisation from Samson as he maintained his balance when he made contact. That was easily put away in the end

Yash Thakur to Samson, no run, Riyan Parag is in. Action will continue. That was a fuller length delivery, Samson drove it on the up and the bowler got his body behind the line for the ball to ricochet on to the sticks. Parag was in
Run-out query sent upstairs. Samson hit that back to the bowler, who got a hand on it and the ball ricocheted on to the sticks. He is in!
Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, gets that through the off-side for a single. Well outside off and Riyan Parag used his hands to slash the ball down to deep cover
Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, no run, has been a decent over so far. Short ball, outside off, Riyan Parag looks to slash and misses. Was banged in, Riyan Parag tried to back away but failed to wood it
Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, wide, loses his radar and has been wided. Very full, well outside off, Riyan Parag looks to chase that and bails out. Easy call for the umpire
Yash Thakur to Samson, 1 run, fuller length delivery, Samson stabs the drive down the ground and gets a single this time as the man at long-on cut it off
Yash Thakur to Samson, 2 runs, drives the ball down the ground and gets a brace. The man at long-on cuts it off
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Samson and Parag looking good. They are strong hitters of the ball and would look for a final hurrah.
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, the wrong 'un, nudged down to long-on for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, pushed down to long-off for a single
Samson in his first match of an IPL season since 2020: 74(32) vs CSK 2020 119(63) vs PK 2021 55(27) vs SRH 2022 55(32) vs SRH 2023 50*(33) vs LSG 2024
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, flatter and at the stumps, punched down to long-on for a single, brings inside edge onto the pads Samson's 21st IPL fifty

Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, a massive top-edge and Mohsin has made a meal of the catch, never looked confident under the skier and didn't even get close - was the wrong 'un and Parag swung across the line, a big top-edge to short fine - Mohsin called for the catch and he's left LSG rue the mistake
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, driven down to long-off for a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, FOUR, lovely', dropped short by Bishnoi - Samson rocks back and then plays a straight-batted drive, through mid-wicket for a boundary, was the wrong 'un, but the length was poor

Summary (Overs 7-12) -- 56/0 -- Krunal keeps it tight from his end -- Runs flow from the other end as Samson, Parag unleash -- Yash Thakur smashed for 21 in his first over -- Bishnoi goes for 15 in his second over
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, tossed up on off, punched down to long-off for a single - Krunal is done with the ball, impressive figures of 0 for 19
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, Krunal drifts one on the leg-stump line, nudged with soft hands towards mid-wicket for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, flatter and at the stumps, whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked through mid-wicket for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, very full and on off, punched down to long-off for a couple
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, no run, tossed up on middle and leg, defended to the on-side
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, dropped short and at the pads, tucked past square leg for a single - another expensive over, 15 came off it
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off - punched square on the off-side for a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, SIX, they're toying with the spinners now - flighted delivery on middle, Samson plants his front-foot forward and then swings through the ine, sends it sailing over long-on for a maximum, brings up RR's 100
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, nudged in front of square on the on-side for a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, SIX, massive, tad too full from Bishnoi - was the attempted wrong 'un, but he's overpitched it - lets Parag gets under it, swing through the line and send it soaring over wide long-on
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, no run, flighted delivery outside off, pushed back at the bowler
Ravi Bishnoi [1.0-0-5-0] is back into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Samson, no run, pushed through by Krunal - Samson went back on the flick and gets an inside edge onto his pad
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, slower and wider of off, pushed down to long-off for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked down to long-on for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, Krunal tosses one just outside off, punched down to long-off for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, nudged in front of square on the on-side for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, leg byes, 1 run, tossed up and sliding into the pads, past Parag's inside edge and rolls in front of short third - he's called through for a quick leg-bye

Yash Thakur to Samson, SIX, 21 off the over, a momentum shifting over? Was a friendly back of a length delivery on middle, Samson picks the length early, swivels across and then pulls it over mid-wicket for another maximum

Yash Thakur to Samson, SIX, hammered, the short-ball plan ain't working for Thakur - banged in short, Samson swivels across, gets on top of the bounce and clears Krunal with the pull, at deep backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Samson, no run, back of a length and at the stumps, punched off the back-foot to cover
Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, 1 run, the bouncer now - kept rising and Parag was in no control over the pull, hit high on the bat and dropped in no man's land at mid-on

Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, SIX, thumped, back of a length and just outside off - Parag plants his front-foot forward and then hammers the pull over wide mid-on, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum
Yash Thakur to Riyan Parag, 2 runs, Thakur starts with a slower cutter, worked with the angle and wide of mid-wicket, runs hard and comes back for the sedcond
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

They've taken the strategic break. Already looking like a new ball pitch, the runs have dried up and the ball ain't coming on when the spinners are in action. Anything around 150-160 could be competitive
Krunal Pandya to Samson, no run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, Samson finds short fine with the flick
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, flatter from Krunal - whipped through mid-wicket for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, pushed through around off, chipped down to long-on for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, played with soft hands and in front of square leg for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, no run, flighted delivery on off, pushed right back at the bowler
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, stays a tad low - Samson stays with the bounce and punches it to the left of the diving bowler - Bishnoi can't stop it and allows a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, no run, another wrong 'un, pushed through flatter and down leg, Samson was shaping for the flick and missed. Called as a wide, but LSG have reviewed - UltraEdge has a spike when the ball is besides the pad, the decision has been reversed
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, chopped away square on the off-side for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, the wrong 'un, Samson plays with the turn and pushes it to long-on, Samson wanted a second and is sent back
Ravi Bishnoi to Riyan Parag, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Samson, 1 run, dragged short by Bishnoi, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Powerplay summary -- Mohsin and Naveen open the attack -- Spidercam issue causes a delay -- Buttler caught behind off Naveen after couple of fours -- Jaiswal gets off to brisk start -- Mohsin gets rid of Jaiswal for 24 -- Pitch is dry and ball is gripping
Parag at #4 in SMAT: 32 inngs 1130 runs Avg 47.08 SR 152.90 12 X 50s
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, flatter and at the pads, clipped in front of square on the on-side for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, Krunal tosses one just outside off, pushed down to long-off for a single
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, worked in front of square on the off-side for a single
Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, turned to the on-side for a single

Krunal Pandya to Riyan Parag, no run, a half-chance, but Samson stays his ground and Krunal ended up colliding into him, giving him no chance for the catch - flighted delivery on off and seemed to have stopped onto Parag - he was trying to check the shot and spooned it back past the non-striker
Krunal Pandya to Samson, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, clipped in front of square on the on-side for a single, brings up RR's 50
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, out Caught by Krunal Pandya!! That's a soft dismissal and RR have lost both openers now. Banged in short and just outside off - Jaiswal was shaping for the pull, the length wasn't short though, cramped him for room and rushed him for pace, lobs a simple catch to mid-on, coming high off the bat. Jaiswal was looking impressive, but his cameo has been cut short. Jaiswal c Krunal Pandya b Mohsin Khan 24(12) [4s-3 6s-1]
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, SIX, cheeky and six, length ball at the stumps - Jaiswal shuffles right across, used the pace on the ball and then lapped it over fine leg, who was inside the ring, sails over the ropes for a maximum
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, tucked in front of square on the on-side for a single

Mohsin Khan to Samson, SIX, clubbed, back of a length and at the body - Samson moves his front-leg away, then gets back into line and whips the pull over backward square leg, has enough to clear the ropes on a the full
Mohsin Khan to Samson, no run, change of pace from Mohsin - rolled his fingers across the seam and pushed one across the right-hander, has Samson poking and beats him on the outside edge
Mohsin Khan to Samson, FOUR, lovely, short of a good length and angling across the right-hander - Samson stands tall and then punches it square on the off-side, past point and runs away to the ropes
Naveen-ul-Haq to Jaiswal, FOUR, cracking shot, fuller length delivery on off - Jaiswal backs away, opens up the off-side and then clatters the drive square past cover, races away to the ropes
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, 1 run, short of a good length and on the pads, nudged in front of square on the on-side for a single
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, Samson leans across and pushes it to the off-side
Naveen-ul-Haq to Samson, no run, on a good length and at the stumps, pushed towards mid-on
We've an issue with one of the zing bails now, it's not lightening up and will have to be replaced. Another delay as the players wait on - Jaiswal has a chat with the umpire and calls for some drinks
Naveen-ul-Haq to Jaiswal, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, pushed in front of mid-off for a quick single
Samson in his first match of an IPL season since 2020: 74(32) vs CSK 2020 119(63) vs PK 2021 55(27) vs SRH 2022 55(32) vs SRH 2023
Naveen-ul-Haq to Jaiswal, 2 runs, length ball at the pads, whipped away off the back-foot past mid-wicket, the fielder in the deep gets across and they come back for the second
Mohsin Khan to Samson, no run, short and wide from Mohsin, draws Samson into a half-hearted waft and he's beaten on the outside edge
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of a good length and angling into the left-hander, flapped away backward of square on the on-side for a single

Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Jaiswal - slower short ball from Mohsin, Jaiswal waits on it, stays on the back-foot and then scythes it backward of square on the off-side for another boundary
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, FOUR, drilled, fuller length delivery outside off - Jaiswal gets forward and hammers it back past the bowler, to the left of mid-off and the ball races away to the ropes
Mohsin Khan to Samson, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, steered with an angled bat to third man
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed in front of mid-on for a quick single
Sanju Samson, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged and caught! That's a body blow for RR - fuller length delivery and in that channel just outside off, Buttler went with hard hands on the drive, gets a thick edge and KL does the rest, moving swiftly to his right and pouching a two-handed low catch - Buttler was looking aggressive, but he's sent packing early. Buttler c Rahul b Naveen-ul-Haq 11(9) [4s-2]
Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, FOUR, a one-handed shovel, but such is the strength on that shot that it almost went all the way - on a good length and angling back into the right-hander, Buttler went hard on the drive, the bottom-hand came off on impact as he skewed it over mid-wicket
Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, no run, the slower ball from Naveen-ul-Haq - Buttler prods forward and steers it with an open face to backward point
Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, no run, on a good length and just outside off, a half-stride forward as Buttler pushed it back at the bowler

Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, FOUR, nicely played, pitched up by Naveen-ul-Haq - Buttler gets half-forward, opens the face of the bat and then slices the drive over backward point, bounces away to the ropes
Naveen-ul-Haq to Buttler, 2 runs, fuller length delivery on off, Buttler leans forward and then pushes it into the gap wide of cover, comes back for the second
Naveen-ul-Haq, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Naveen ul-Haq to share the new ball
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, no run, lovely, on a good length and in that channel just outside off - draws Jaiswal forward and then seams away enough to beat the outside edge
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, 1 run, on a good length and angling across the right-hander, pushed through cover for a single
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, no run, short of a good length and at the stumps, Buttler presses across defensively
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, wide, short and miled wide of off, Buttler chases and then pulls his bat back, called as a wide
Mohsin Khan to Buttler, no run, short of a good length and just outside off - Buttler hops across and defends it back at the bowler

A delay as the wire of the spider cam has snapped. It's taking some time to sort it out. The LSG players huddle along as we await the resumption. Sanju Samson and Riyan Parag have padded up, RR's 3 and 4 this match and probably for the season. This is taking a lot of time as they set things right, but we're ready now
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off - Jaiswal inner halves the drive to the right of mid-on - Krunal lumbers across, dives and keeps them down to a single
Mohsin Khan to Jaiswal, no run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander, Jaiswal swivels across on the pull and missed, off the thigh-pad and bounced to the off-side
Jaiswal and Buttler are at the crease. Jaiswal is on strike. Mohsin Khan will open the attack
